d 'XTQRPLOT': module to compute entity-specific marginal effects from panel quantile regression
d
d  xtqrplot estimates panel quantile regression across a
d user-defined grid of quantile windows and produces
d entity-specific marginal effect visualisations. For each
d cross-sectional unit, the command identifies its percentile rank
d in the distribution of the dependent variable, assigns it to the
d nearest quantile window, extracts the corresponding coefficient,
d and presents the result as a colour-coded bar chart or matrix
d heat map with 95% confidence intervals. The package supports both
d balanced and unbalanced panels, four effect types (raw
d coefficient, semi-elasticity, elasticity, basis points), three
d plot types (cross-section, time-dimension, panel x time heat
d map), pre-estimation normality diagnostics, and automatic results
d tables. An optional enhanced heat map is available if heatplot
d (SSC) is installed. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: quantile regression
d KW: marginal effects
d
d Requires: Stata version 14 and xtqreg or qregpd from SSC (q.v.)
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260403
d
d Author: Noman Arshed,   Sunway Business School, Sunway University
d Support: email nouman.arshed@@gmail.com
d
